# MeshScale AI Agent

When helping with MeshScale, follow the MeshScale AI Agent Complete Guide.

## Architecture
- **CLI (meshscale)** – deploys, configures, manages
- **Control Plane (meshscale-cp)** – runs infrastructure.swift every 500ms, schedules, reconciles
- **Workers (meshscale-worker)** – run Docker, provision containers
- Communication via Convex; Netbird mesh for networking

## Resource Syntax
- `@Resource` structs conform to PostgresDatabase, HTTPService, WebService, BackgroundWorker, RedisCache, MessageQueue, ObjectStorage, StaticSite
- Use `@Dependency var x: ResourceType` for co-location hints
- `latencySensitivity`: `.high` (co-locate), `.medium` (prefer), `.low` (anywhere)

## Key Rules
- Databases > 200GB or > 15k QPS → use ShardingConfig
- Single instance DBs → VolumeConfig with backend (.awsEBS, .longhorn, etc.)
- Add resources in dependency order in main()
- PortFiltering(80, 443) for inbound, PortFiltering(.all) for outbound

## CLI
- `meshscale deploy`, `meshscale deploy --watch`
- `meshscale auth login` / `meshscale auth logout`
- `meshscale worker setup --type general`, `meshscale worker setup-ami`, `meshscale worker status`
- `meshscale control-plane setup --region us-east-1`
- `meshscale volumes list|inspect|migrate|backup`
- `meshscale logs <project>`
